The atmosphere and the live music was so wonderful, it just took me back home - to Azerbaijan. The staff was very friendly. However, the bathroom and overall place was not very clean. I think this place needs some renovation. Also there was a lady, I am not sure if manager or owner who saw me putting my leftover food in my to-go box and then yelled the waiter why he doesn't help me with that. Since I had several leftovers, I wanted to organize them by myself and that is what I told the waiter too when he approached me (even for no reason I would still keep doing it by myself after hearing her yelling). She could have just simply approach me, offer help or just can communicate to the staff politely. Well, I am not sure if I will go back or not but if you happen to go there make sure you leave generous tip for waiter and live music person.  To the owner: Please make this place nicer and cleaner and get/provide some training on customer service. There are no many places serving such a good food. I am sure there are many Azerbaijanians, including me who are more than ready/happy to buy good Azerbaijani food and service and support the business providing that combination.
